name: HIIT Workout
description: High intensity interval training (HIIT) takes advantage of short, micro bursts of very high intensity exercise, coupled with a short duration of timed recovery. HIIT protocols are very powerful in that they create an “in workout” oxygen deficit in an effort to create EPOC, or excess post-exercise oxygen consumption.

name: Yoga
description: The ancient discipline from Indid has gained status across the globe. With simple stretches and controlled breathing to complex and fast changing postures, yoga has a wide range of exercise to offer various age group.

name: Pilates
description: Beginners to fitness nerds, Pilates can be tailored as per one's fitness index. It is based on Six Principals of cantering, control,flow, breath, precision and cencentration.

name: Strength training
description: An essential part of improving strength and muscular endurance, resistance training can incorporate body weight, TRX Suspension Training, free weights, weight machines, etc. Traditional strength training techniques, including super sets

name: Cross Fit
description: This is a highly intensity workout that has garnered attention of many fitness enthusiasts over the last two decades. It involves varied functional movements performed at anaerobic level with goal of strength buildong & conditioning.

name: Aerobic
description: Aerobic is an umbrella term spanning across various fitness exercise that can make your body sweat profusely, lungs beat faster and cardiovascular system pump the blood faster.
